<exercise number="65"><statement><p>Prove the product rule by following the steps. <ol label="a">
    <li>Suppose <m>z_1=a+bi</m> and <m>z_2=c+di</m>. Compute <m>z_1z_2</m>.</li>
    <li>Now suppose that <m>z_1=r(\cos \alpha +i \sin \alpha)</m> and <m>z_2=R(\cos \beta +i \sin \beta)</m>.  Write <m>a,~b,~c</m> and <m>d</m> in terms of <m>r,~R,~\alpha</m> and <m>\beta</m>.</li>
    <li>Substitute your expressions for <m>a,~b,~c</m> and <m>d</m> into your formula for <m>z_1z_2</m>.</li>
    <li>Use the laws of sines and cosines to simplify your answer to part (c).</li></ol> </p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><m>z_1z_2 = (ac-bd) + (ad+bc)i</m></li>
    <li><m>a=r\cos\alpha,~b=r\sin\alpha,~c=R\cos\beta,~d=R\sin\beta</m></li>
    <li><m>(ac-bd) + (ad+bc)i = (rR\cos\alpha\cos\beta - rR\sin\alpha\sin\beta)</m>
        <m> + (rR\cos\alpha\sin\beta+rR\sin\alpha\cos\beta)i</m></li>
    <li><m>rR(\cos (\alpha+\beta) +i\sin (\alpha+\beta))</m></li></ol>
</p></answer></exercise>

